translated: Ysander, Bengt Daniel, vicar, Kungsbacka, b. 9/1/90 in Tölö, Halland county, son of vicar Bengt Y. and Amanda Wetterqvist. Married on 18 with Anna-Lisa Bergström. — Passed student examination in Gothenburg in 1910, theological philosophy examination in 1911, theological candidate and practical theological examination in Uppsala in 1915, ordained priest in Gothenburg in 1916. Parish adjunct in Gällstad in 1916, Ljungby in 1916, pastor and rural dean in Seglora from 1916 to 1918, curate in Holsljunga from 1918 to 1933, vicar of Kungsbacka and Hanhals since 1933. Chairman of the city council since 1939, chairman of the church council, church assembly, church meeting, board of primary school, RKs Kungsbacka district, member of the board for Katrinebergs folk high school since 1939, inspector for secondary school since 1944. Knight of the Royal Order of Vasa since 1940.
